<DOC><DOCNO> AP890823-0058 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-23-89 0946EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--MayorArrested     08-23 0149</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Mayor Arrested,0152</SECOND><HEAD>Mayor Arrested On Cocaine Charges</HEAD><DATELINE>PARKIN, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   FBI agents arrested the mayor on cocainecharges after a three-year investigation into local drug trafficking.   Mayor Tommy Voyles, 43, was freed on $50,000 bond Tuesday afterappearing before a U.S. magistrate. The mayor, who was elected in1986, made no comment as he was led in handcuffs into the federalcourthouse.   ``It's just a tragedy. We hate to see drug-related accusations ofpublic corruption,'' U.S. Attorney Chuck Banks said.   Charges against Voyles were in an eight-count indictment issuedby a federal grand jury. The charges include one count of conspiringto distribute cocaine and seven counts of cocaine distribution from1987 though 1989, FBI spokesman Ron Wolfe said.   A separate indictment charges that Voyles conspired to distributecocaine with William Criswell, 50, a used-car dealer, Wolfe said.Criswell was released Tuesday on his own recognizance.</TEXT></DOC>